casebody.data:
No. 111,

Orig.

Delaware v. New York.

Motions for additional time for oral argument and for divided argument granted in part and denied in part. An additional 10 minutes are allotted for oral argument. The time for oral argument is divided as follows: 20 minutes for Delaware; 20 minutes for New York; and 30 minutes for one attorney in support of the Report of the Special Master. [For earlier order herein, see, e. g., ante, p. 805.]
